plot: An ambitious and charismatic Black senator campaigning for the presidency falls ill from a mysterious malady, possibly AIDS.

House is convinced a Black presidential candidate has AIDS, but the senator's passion convinces him otherwise. Also, Vogler forces House to give a speech endorsing a new drug from Vogler's company, but House has plans of his own. Clinic Cases: A woman showing signs of having had a miscarriage claims she's not having sex despite a hickey and carpet burns on her backside.—llastsonkrypton
